track_notes: Park in the layby/passing place. Along the road, right up the track towards the old house/barn. Landowner appears to have removed all public right of way signs. Through gate facing you. Break right in the steep up hill field to track that bends left into the woods at a farm gate. Follow narrow path up through dense, then more open woodland. After a small descent (muddy at bottom), pick up a track going right uphill. Follow to summit. Pleasant bench to sit on.
track_title: Allt y Main from the north

track_notes: This route deviates from that of MW0WML (which has become over-grown) at SJ16241563, where you simply keeping following the more-obvious track ENE. This takes you, after 400m, to a field gate. In the field head to the south-most corner. From here there is a good path which rejoins the other track and takes you onwards to the summit.

I parked on the verge at SJ151141 (just enough space to reverse a car in at 90 degrees to the road).  Follow tarmac road eastwards, keep right at Brook House and go down into the dip and continueup to gate at SJ151141 - this seems to be a well used alternative parking spot.
Follow forest road to SJ166154 (passing below the summit) then follow good path eastwards up to summit.

Parking for 3-4 cars in large layby on the A495.  Follow track signposted as bridleway off the main road up to house,  path goes around the north side of the house, follow zig zags up slope to clearing at end of forest track.  Continue up the track to meet main forest track, turn sharp right and continue along track until you reach narrow grassy/muddy path on the left.  Follow this to the summit.
